<quiz>
  <question type="stack">
    <name>
      <text>Finding the area of a rectangular school garden</text>
    </name>
    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<p>
A school is preparing a rectangular garden for planting {@crop@}. The garden measures {@l@} m in length and {@w@} m in width. Find the area of the garden.
</p>

<p>
Give your answer correct to <b>2 decimal places</b>.
</p>

<p>
Area = [[input:ans1]] \(\text {m}^2\) [[validation:ans1]] [[feedback:prt1]]
</p>]]></text>
    </questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<h3>Worked Solution</h3>

<p>
The garden is rectangular.
</p>

<p>
The formula for the area of a rectangle is:
</p>

<p>
\[
A = l \times w
\]
</p>

<p>
Step 1: Identify the dimensions.
</p>

<p>
\[
l = {@l@}\text{ m}, \quad w = {@w@}\text{ m}
\]
</p>

<p>
Step 2: Substitute into the formula.
</p>

<p>
\[
A = {@l@} \times {@w@}
\]
</p>

<p>
Step 3: Multiply.
</p>

<p>
\[
A = {@A@}
\]
</p>

<p>
Step 4: Round to 2 decimal places.
</p>

<p>
\[
A \approx {@A_round@}\text{ m}^2
\]
</p>

<p>
Therefore, the area of the garden is:
</p>

<p>
\[
\boxed{{@A_round@}\text{ m}^2}
\]
</p>]]></text>
    </generalfeedback>
